1. e4 { [%clk 0:55:35] } 1... c6 { [%clk 0:59:59] } 2. d4 { [%clk 0:55:08] } 2... d5 { [%clk 0:59:53] } 3. exd5 { [%clk 0:55:03] } 3... cxd5 { [%clk 0:59:42] } 4. Bd3 { [%clk 0:54:58] } 4... Nc6 { [%clk 0:59:28] } 5. c3 { [%clk 0:54:48] } 5... Nf6 { [%clk 0:59:15] } 6. h3 { [%clk 0:54:34] } (6. Bf4 Bg4 { [%csl Gg4,Gd1] } 7. Qb3 Na5 { [%csl Ga5] } (7... Qd7) 8. Qb5+ Bd7 9. Qc5 e5) 6... e5 { [%clk 0:59:00] } (6... Bg4) 7. dxe5 { [%clk 0:54:24] } 7... Nxe5 { [%clk 0:58:45] } 8. Nf3 { [%clk 0:53:49] } 8... Nxd3+ { [%clk 0:57:26] } 9. Qxd3 { [%clk 0:53:34] } 9... Bc5 { First move out of theory. Should have played Bd6. I considered this (since I didn't remember) but the bishop seemed more active here and I wanted to keep eyes on the d5 pawn. Apparently 10. Be3 would then be undesirable given that I don't want to exchange my dark bishop here. } { [%clk 0:54:20] } (9... Bd6 10. O-O O-O 11. Bg5 h6 (11... Be7) 12. Bxf6 { [%csl Gd5] } 12... Qxf6 13. Qxd5 Rd8 14. Qh5 (14. Nbd2 Bh2+ { [%csl Gd5] }) 14... b5 15. Qxb5 (15. Nbd2 Bb7) 15... Ba6 { [%csl Gf1] } 16. Qxa6 Bh2+) 10. O-O { [%clk 0:52:54] } 10... O-O { First thing hide the king! } { [%clk 0:53:46] } 11. Bg5 { Be3 was indeed not played but this seemed annoying to me. I can't move the queen or I get my pawns doubled and if I don't protect my d5 pawn he can take the f6 knight and once I take back with my queen I lose the pawn. } { [%clk 0:51:42] } 11... Be6 { Need to protect the pawn somehow and the bishop can't really go anywhere else. } { [%clk 0:48:37] } (11... Qd6 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. Qxd5) (11... h6 12. Bxf6 Qxf6) 12. Nbd2 { [%clk 0:48:04] } 12... h6 { As already mentioned that bishop is giving me some problems so I wanted to try to kick it out. } { [%clk 0:45:56] } 13. Bh4 { Seems like the best move. I was hoping he would either trade or move off the diagonal. } { [%clk 0:43:44] } 13... Rc8 { I considered g4 but rejected it as too weakening, so I played Rc8 instead. It felt aimless since the rook might belong on a8 for future queenside play. Re8 would have made more sense on the fully open file. } { [%clk 0:41:33] } 14. Nb3 { [%clk 0:43:26] } 14... Bd6 { Considered Be6 too but I had a small plan with this move: } { [%clk 0:37:48] } 15. Bxf6 { I didn't see this coming. I feel like trading that bishop off only helped me as that pin was quite a problem in my position. } { [%clk 0:39:42] } (15. Rac1 g5 16. Bg3 Bxg3 17. fxg3 { Doubling white's pawns and opening a diagonal to the king } { [%csl Bg3,Bg2][%cal Ra7g1] }) 15... Qxf6 { I felt like my queen could have been happier elsewhere but with the trade of the bishop for my knight I can't complain. } { [%clk 0:36:56] } 16. Qd4 { I felt like trading queens was forced because of the attack on my a7 pawn. } { [%clk 0:37:26] } 16... Qxd4 { [%clk 0:35:28] } 17. Nbxd4 { [%clk 0:36:53] } 17... Rfe8 { Just trying to develop and I didn't feel like moving my bishop made much sense since it can only go to d7. } { [%csl Be6] [%clk 0:33:39] } 18. Rfe1 { [%clk 0:36:38] } (18. Nxe6 fxe6 { This just seemed to fix my isolated pawn "problem". }) 18... Re7 { I couldn't really think of any interesting plans here so I just went for the doubling of rooks on the one fully open file. } { [%clk 0:32:13] } 19. Re2 { [%clk 0:32:23] } 19... Rce8 { [%clk 0:31:26] } 20. Rae1 { [%clk 0:31:21] } 20... a6 { Wanted to stop Nh5 from ever happening. } { [%clk 0:31:00] } 21. Kf1 { [%clk 0:28:49] } 21... g6 { Since white started bringing their king to the middle I thought I'd copy by first giving my king a square to go to. } { [%clk 0:30:55] } 22. Nxe6 { [%clk 0:21:58] } 22... fxe6 { As mentioned earlier this means I no longer have an isolated pawn. I also thought either one of these pawns could become a passer at some point. } { [%clk 0:27:46] } 23. Ne5 { I didn't consider this much because I couldn't see where the knight would go next. } { [%clk 0:18:08] } 23... Kg7 { [%clk 0:25:31] } 24. b3 { [%clk 0:14:43] } 24... Rf8 { The idea here was to then play Bc5 and increase my pressure on the f2 pawn. } { [%cal Gd6c5] [%clk 0:23:01] } 25. Nd3 { This stopped Bc5 and I had missed it. Now I don't have a plan anymore and my pawn is under attack. } { [%clk 0:10:24] } 25... Rc7 { Here I knew I was gambling. I spent some time calculating but couldn't really see if I was going to be winning or losing at the end. It felt like the only way to make something more concrete happen so i went for it. } { [%clk 0:13:19] } 26. Rxe6 { [%clk 0:09:34] } 26... Rxc3 { [%clk 0:13:09] } 27. Rxd6 { [%clk 0:09:28] } 27... Rxd3 { [%clk 0:12:59] } 28. Re7+ { [%clk 0:08:56] } 28... Rf7 { [%clk 0:12:23] } 29. Rxf7+ { [%clk 0:07:38] } 29... Kxf7 { This was as far as I had seen and I missed that he could play Rd6+ winning another pawn. } { [%clk 0:12:11] } 30. Rd7+ { [%clk 0:07:38] } 30... Kf6 { [%clk 0:10:58] } 31. Rxb7 { [%clk 0:06:44] } 31... Ke5 { At this point I thought I had made a mistake with 25... Rc7 therefore I decided to bring the king forward and fully gamble on my d5 pawn promoting instead of trying to defend the other pawns. } { [%clk 0:09:18] } 32. Ke2 { [%clk 0:06:22] } 32... Kd4 { [%clk 0:08:57] } 33. Rb4+ { [%clk 0:06:10] } 33... Kc3 { [%clk 0:08:27] } 34. Rg4 { This seemed incorrect. How is he going to stop my pawn from promoting? } { [%clk 0:05:43] } 34... Rd2+ { [%clk 0:08:15] } (34... d4 35. Rxg6 Rd2+ 36. Ke1 Rxa2 37. Rd6 d3 { I can't see how he will stop the pawn without sacrificing his rook. }) 35. Ke1 { [%clk 0:04:22] } 35... d4 { [%clk 0:07:02] } 36. Rxg6 { [%clk 0:02:42] } 36... Rxa2 { [%clk 0:06:37] } 37. Rg3+ { This again seemed wrong. He is just helping me move my pawn forward. } { [%clk 0:02:34] } (37. Rc6+) 37... d3 { [%clk 0:06:19] } 38. f4 { I think he should have gone for this idea much sooner. It might have given him a chance to sack his rook for my pawn and then promote his own pawn. } { [%clk 0:02:32] } 38... Ra1+ { [%clk 0:05:09] } 39. Kf2 { [%clk 0:02:32] } 39... Kc2 { [%clk 0:04:53] } 40. Rg6 { [%clk 0:01:53] } 40... d2 { [%clk 0:04:22] } 41. Rc6+ { [%clk 0:01:53] } 41... Kb2 { I didn't want to play Kxb3 as it seemed like it might open me up to too many checks. } { [%clk 0:03:58] } 0-1


