1. e4 { [%clk 0:59:54] } 1... e5 { [%clk 0:59:58] } 2. Nf3 { [%clk 0:59:48] } 2... Nc6 { [%clk 0:59:51] } 3. Bc4 { [%clk 0:59:41] } 3... Nf6 { [%clk 0:58:58] } 4. Ng5 { [%clk 0:59:35] } 4... d5 { [%clk 0:56:29] } 5. exd5 { [%clk 0:59:02] } 5... Nxd5 { Always happy when this happens. } { [%clk 0:55:39] } 6. Nxf7 { [%clk 0:58:35] } 6... Kxf7 { [%clk 0:52:10] } 7. Qf3+ { [%clk 0:57:56] } 7... Qf6 { I don't think I've ever seen this specific move before. But I thought for a minute and realized that after Bd5 I will transpose to the line I know. } { [%clk 0:50:55] } (7... Ke8 8. Bxd5 Qf6 9. Bxc6+ Qxc6 10. Qxc6+) 8. Bxd5+ { [%clk 0:56:12] } 8... Ke8 { [%clk 0:49:42] } 9. Bxc6+ { [%clk 0:55:39] } 9... Qxc6 { [%clk 0:49:17] } 10. Qxc6+ { [%clk 0:55:32] } 10... bxc6 { And this is just a great position for me. Up 1 pawn plus doubled pawns on the c file. } { [%csl Bc6,Bc7] [%clk 0:48:29] } 11. d3 { Thought about castling but since there is no rush I felt like this move made sense to allow my bishop to come out if needed. } { [%clk 0:55:29] } 11... h6 { This seemed slow. Very slow. I already had a better position and if he let's me get free moves everything will start falling. } { [%clk 0:47:45] } 12. O-O { [%clk 0:55:09] } 12... Bc5 { [%clk 0:47:11] } 13. Nd2?? { Here I consider this move a blunder. The reason why is that I wanted to play Re1 but I thought that after 13. ... O-O black would get his king out of the way and create an attack on my f2 pawn. So to avoid this I went for Nd2 with the intention of blocking the rook's view with Nf3. Only problem being that black can't castle! If I had played Re1 then black playing ... Rf8 would simply lose him another pawn. } { [%clk 0:53:54] } 13... Rf8 { [%clk 0:46:14] } 14. Nf3 { [%clk 0:53:47] } 14... Bd6 { Only sensible move in my opinion but that pawn was going to fall at some point. } { [%clk 0:44:32] } 15. Re1 { [%clk 0:53:21] } 15... Kf7 { This was a surprise. I had calculated 15. ... Rf5 } { [%clk 0:42:13] } (15... Rf5 16. Nd4 Rh5 17. Nxc6) 16. Nxe5+ { [%clk 0:52:56] } 16... Bxe5 { [%clk 0:41:40] } 17. Rxe5 { [%clk 0:52:49] } 17... Kg8 { [%clk 0:41:26] } 18. Bd2 { [%clk 0:52:14] } 18... Rb8 { [%clk 0:40:52] } 19. Bc3 { [%clk 0:51:41] } 19... Rf7 { [%clk 0:39:42] } 20. Rae1 { [%clk 0:51:12] } 20... Bd7 { [%clk 0:39:21] } 21. h3 { Wanted to avoid any back rank problems. } { [%clk 0:50:45] } 21... Rb5 { [%clk 0:39:01] } 22. Re7 { [%clk 0:50:13] } 22... Rbf5 { [%clk 0:37:25] } 23. Rxf7 { I thought trading was only going to help me because I had a clear static advantage. } { [%clk 0:49:04] } 23... Rxf7 { [%clk 0:37:08] } 24. Be5 { [%clk 0:48:25] } 24... Re7 { I saw this and thought that after Kf1 it's not a problem and the c7 pawn is threatened again. } { [%clk 0:35:39] } 25. Kf1 { [%clk 0:48:19] } 25... Be6 { [%clk 0:35:52] } 26. Bxc7 { [%clk 0:47:39] } 26... Kf7 { [%clk 0:35:01] } (26... Rxc7 27. Rxe6) 27. Bd6 { Now I had to move my bishop and I couldn't see why anything else was better than Bd6. } { [%clk 0:46:34] } 27... Rd7 { [%clk 0:34:47] } 28. Bc5 { [%clk 0:46:20] } 28... Bxa2 { I thought this wasn't a threat from a distance because of b3 and then Ra1. } { [%clk 0:34:02] } 29. b3 { [%clk 0:46:08] } 29... Rd5 { This was the only move I thought gave him a chance. But instead of defending my bishop in any way I just opted for the trade of bishops with Ra1 right away. I think in hindsight this was the move I would most want to change. The rook endgame ended up being much harder than I thought it would. } { [%clk 0:28:57] } 30. Ra1 { [%clk 0:46:03] } 30... Rxc5 { [%clk 0:28:57] } 31. Rxa2 { [%clk 0:45:49] } 31... a5 { [%clk 0:27:56] } 32. g4 { [%clk 0:45:01] } 32... g5 { [%clk 0:27:29] } 33. Kg2 { [%clk 0:44:45] } 33... Kf6 { [%clk 0:27:21] } 34. Kg3 { [%clk 0:44:22] } 34... Ke5 { [%clk 0:26:29] } 35. h4 { [%clk 0:40:38] } 35... gxh4+ { [%clk 0:26:23] } 36. Kxh4 { Here I thought I was still doing great. } { [%clk 0:40:22] } 36... Kf4 { This move I missed tho and it definitely seemed a bit scary. } { [%clk 0:26:10] } 37. d4 { [%clk 0:39:04] } 37... Rg5 { [%clk 0:25:50] } 38. c4 { [%clk 0:38:19] } 38... Rxg4+ { [%clk 0:25:14] } 39. Kh5 { [%clk 0:38:11] } 39... Kf3 { [%clk 0:22:42] } 40. Kxh6 { [%clk 0:36:48] } 40... Rxd4 { At this point I was very scared. I thought this might very well be a draw. } { [%clk 0:22:39] } 41. Kg5 { [%clk 0:35:57] } 41... Rd3 { [%clk 0:21:58] } 42. Rb2 { [%clk 0:35:28] } 42... c5 { [%clk 0:21:36] } 43. Kf5 { [%clk 0:32:03] } 43... Rc3 { [%clk 0:20:53] } 44. Ke5 { [%clk 0:32:00] } 44... Rd3 { [%clk 0:20:53] } 45. Ke6 { Him repeating moves didn't seem right tho because like this I can slowly bring my king closer. I was looking at Ra2 followed by trading the a pawn for the b pawn but then winning the c pawn. And by first going Ke6 I force him to move his rook off the 3rd rank which buys me a tempo. } { [%clk 0:30:59] } 45... Rd4 { [%clk 0:19:56] } 46. Ra2 { [%clk 0:30:46] } 46... Rd3 { Now I can go for the same idea and black is a move behind. } { [%clk 0:19:48] } 47. Rxa5 { [%clk 0:30:26] } 47... Rxb3 { [%clk 0:19:38] } 48. Rxc5 { [%clk 0:30:22] } 48... Kxf2 { [%clk 0:19:36] } 49. Rd5 { [%clk 0:29:52] } 49... Rb4 { [%clk 0:19:30] } 50. c5 { [%clk 0:29:45] } 50... Rc4 { [%clk 0:19:04] } 51. Kd6 { [%clk 0:29:20] } 51... Ke3 { [%clk 0:19:04] } 52. c6 { [%clk 0:28:17] } 52... Ke4 { After this move by him I regretted not playing Kd7 instead of Kd6. I thought this might be a draw since I can't advance my pawn: } { [%clk 0:19:04] } 53. Rh5 { [%clk 0:27:14] } 53... Kf4 { [%clk 0:19:01] } 54. Rh6 { [%clk 0:26:50] } 54... Kg5 { [%clk 0:18:53] } 55. Re6 { [%clk 0:26:25] } 55... Kf5 { [%clk 0:18:53] } 56. Kd7 { This whole rook reroute allowed me to advance my king as I didn't see a way to make that happen with the rook on e5. } { [%clk 0:26:13] } 56... Rc5 { [%clk 0:18:45] } 57. Rd6 { [%clk 0:25:16] } 57... Ke5 { Here I finally felt like I could actually see the win. } { [%clk 0:18:44] } 58. Rd1 { With this move his king will never get close to the pawn and his rook will never check my king. I definitely wondered if I could have reached something similar earlier... } { [%clk 0:24:57] } 58... Rb5 { [%clk 0:16:41] } 59. c7 { [%clk 0:24:39] } 59... Rb7 { This also seemed like it was doing nothing for him. } { [%clk 0:16:41] } 60. Kd8 { After this move he can't stop the promotion. } { [%clk 0:24:21] } 60... Rxc7 { GG } { [%clk 0:15:13] } (60... Rb8+ 61. cxb8=Q+) 61. Kxc7 { [%clk 0:24:15] } 61... Ke6 62. Rd2 Ke5 63. Kc6 Ke6 64. Re2+ Kf5 65. Kd6 Kf4 66. Kd5 Kf3 67. Re8 Kf4 68. Re7 Kf5 69. Rf7+ Kg4 70. Ke5 Kg3 71. Ke4 Kg4 72. Rg7+ Kh3 73. Kf4 Kh2 74. Kf3 Kh1 75. Kf2 Kh2 76. Rh7# 1-0


