was the only option since the bishop was pinned to the rook. } { [%clk 0:40:00] } 19... Bh4 { [%clk 0:48:00] } 20. Bf2 { Here I was quite happy. I had looked at the few options black had and they all seemed better for me. Taking the bishops allows M2, moving the bishop from h4 allows M2 and taking my rook seemed fine. } { [%clk 0:40:00] } 20... Rxe2 { Only move. } { [%clk 0:47:00] } (20... Bxf2 21. Rxe8+ Rxe8 22. Rxe8#) (20... Bf6 21. Rxe8+ Rxe8 22. Rxe8#) 21. Rxe2 { [%clk 0:40:00] } 21... Bg5 { [%clk 0:45:00] } 22. Be3 { Here I went with this move because I was scared of the pressure black could create with Rd8 attacking my pinned knight. With this move Rd8 wasn't possible anymore but it did allow Re8. } { [%clk 0:39:00] } 22... Re8 { [%clk 0:43:00] } 23. Nf1 { Here I felt like I was forced to play this move to defend my pinned bishop. } { [%clk 0:36:00] } (23. Nc4 b5 { I thought this was completely losing. }) 23... Bd7 { [%clk 0:41:00] } 24. Kd1? { And here came my first big mistake. 23. ... Bd7 seemed like a move without a point to it. Bus obviously I missed the idea of going Bb5. } { [%clk 0:36:00] } (24. b3 Bb5 25. c4) (24. c4 Bb5) 24... Bb5 { This hurt because it could have been so easily avoided with something like b3 and c4 or even c4 right away. } { [%clk 0:40:00] } 25. Rd2 { Here I thought I was losing but not by a lot. } { [%clk 0:34:00] } 25... Bf6 { Bf6 caught me off guard since now some threats are renewed by black and I couldn't find a great way to deal with everyone of them. } { [%clk 0:36:00] } (25... Bxe3 26. Nxe3 Rxe3 27. Rd8+ Re8 28. Rxe8+ { This obviously wouldn't have worked out for black. }) (25... Bxf1 26. Bxg5 { This seemed great too as I was still up a pawn. }) 26. Re2 { [%clk 0:29:00] } 26... Bxe2+ { [%clk 0:36:00] } 27. Kxe2 { Losing the exchange but I thought I had decent chances of holding this position. } { [%clk 0:29:00] } 27... Bg5 { [%clk 0:35:00] } 28. Kd3 { [%clk 0:27:00] } 28... Bxe3 { [%clk 0:35:00] } 29. Nxe3 { [%clk 0:27:00] } 29... Rd8+ { [%clk 0:35:00] } 30. Ke2 { Here I was quite unhappy but as I already mentioned definitely some hopes of holding this endgame. } { [%clk 0:26:00] } 30... Kf8 { [%clk 0:34:00] } 31. b4 { [%clk 0:26:00] } 31... g6 { [%clk 0:32:00] } 32. a4 { Taking space on the queenside, I didn't see what else I could play for. } { [%clk 0:25:00] } 32... h5 { And after this move my opponent offered a draw. There was no way I was going to win this and even trying to draw it would have been quite difficult in my opoinion. } { [%clk 0:28:00] } 1/2-1/2


