1. e4 c6 2. Nc3 d5 { Big think here to decide whether I should play Qf3 or Nf3. } 3. Nf3 $146 { Let's trust coach! } 3... dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 5. Qe2 Nxe4 6. Qxe4 Nd7 7. Bc4 e6 { First move out of my new repertoire. The line I have goes as follows. } (7... Nf6 { [%cal Gf6e4] } 8. Ne5 e6 (8... Nxe4 9. Bxf7#) 9. Qe2) 8. d4 Nf6 9. Qe2 { Never studied this line but since I know it quite well as black I made it here. } 9... Bd6 10. O-O { Considered c3 but didn't see why I shouldn't castle first. } 10... O-O 11. c3 { c3 now made sense. I want to solidify my center. } 11... b5 { Expected this move as it's his only try to free up the c8 bishop. } 12. Bd3 { I was considering playing Bb3 to then go Bc2 and possibly bring my queen to d3 but I realized that on d3 the bishop is instantly better while going through b3 wastes a tempo. Also the bishop can get to c2 equally as fast from here. } 12... Bb7 { Here I saw a problem for black. } 13. Bg5 { If the knight gets traded I can play Qe4 with a double threat. } 13... h6 { I thought this was great for me as I would have most likely taken no matter what black played. This was just a loss of tempo. } (13... c5) 14. Bxf6 Qxf6 15. Qe4 { Double attack of checkmate on h7 and the b5 pawn. } { [%cal Gc6b5] } 15... g6 { [%csl Gb5] } (15... Rab8 16. Qh7#) 16. Bxb5 cxb5 (16... Rab8 17. Bxc6 Bxc6 18. Qxc6 Rxb2 { This would have been a problem if the bishop wasn't hanging. }) (16... Rac8 { This looked like black's best reply. }) 17. Qxb7 { Now I'm just up a pawn and I saw no good counterplay for black. } { [%csl Gb7] } 17... Qf4 { Here I got a little scared. I saw no threat and couldn't understand the idea. Black gives up another pawn but why. } 18. Qxb5 Rfb8 { Again I was confused. I wanted to bring my queen back to e2 and this just helped. } (18... g5 19. Qe2 (19. h3 { This would have saved my knight. }) 19... g4 20. g3 gxf3 21. gxf4 fxe2 22. Rfe1 Bxf4 { I thought this was the idea. }) 19. Qe2 Rb5 { I hadn't considered this move for black. } 20. Qd2 { When I played this move I was very happy. I felt like the Queen trade was forced. Also I saw the potential knight fork if after trading queens black took my b2 pawn. } { [%csl Gd2] } (20. Qxb5) 20... Qxd2 (20... Qh4 { Black can't defend h6 or attack h2 in any way }) (20... Qf6 21. Qxh6 { Here I would just be up 3 pawns. } 21... Rxb2 22. Ng5 { Pawn hunting wouldn't have helped him much. }) 21. Nxd2 Rxb2 22. Nc4 { :) } { [%cal Gd6a3] } 22... Bxh2+ { This hangs a whole bishop for 1 or 2 pawns. } { [%csl Gh2] } (22... Ba3 23. Nxa3 { This hangs a whole bishop. }) (22... Rb6 23. Nxb6 axb6 { This hangs an exchange. }) 23. Kxh2 Rc2 24. Kg1 { Wanted to defend my f2 pawn and free up my f1 rook. } 24... Rc8 25. Ne3 { I thought about playing Ne5 instead but I liked that with this move I forced black to take with the rook on c2 losing control of the 2nd rank. } 25... R8xc3 { My opponent didn't like that idea and wanted to maintain control of the 2nd rank... } 26. Nxc2 Rxc2 27. Rfd1 Kg7 28. d5 exd5 { [%csl Gd1] } 29. Rxd5 h5 30. Ra5 Rc7 { This made me with I had played 30. Rd7 } 31. Rd1 h4 32. Rd3 Rc1+ 33. Kh2 Rc2 34. Rf3 { With the threat on f7 if black allows me to take the a7 pawn. } 34... Rc7 35. Kh3 Kh6 36. Kxh4 f5 37. Rfa3 Rc4+ 38. Kg3 Kg5 39. Rxa7 { I was a little scared to play this move but I saw no threats on my king. } 39... Rg4+ 40. Kh2 f4 41. R7a5+ Kf6 42. Rf3 { Pinning the pawn with the idea of playing g3. } 42... g5 43. g3 Kg6 44. Kh3 Kh5 { Forced as the rook is trapped. } 45. Rxf4 { The pawn is pinned so black is forced to take with the rook, leaving me with a rook and some pawns vs just a lone king. } 45... Rxf4 46. gxf4 (46. Rxg5+ Kxg5 47. gxf4+ Kxf4 { Considered this but I'm not cocky enough to trust my intuition or calculation this much. }) 46... Kg6 47. Rxg5+ { With the idea of playing Re5 after black moves his king to the f file. I would then have pushed my a pawn, made a queen and attempted a ladder mate but instead hung stalemate. Luckily he resigned. } 1-0


