clk 0:54:00] } 32. g5 { 10 minute think. This seemed like a very critical moment as I knew she would play Bg2 soon and I needed my pawn to create a threat fast. } { [%clk 0:26:00] } (32. f5 { I considered this too but I didn't really see a continuation after Bg2 } 32... Bg2 33. Nxf7+ Ke7 34. Ng5 { I had this which defended my pawn. Looking at it now it doesn't look too bad actually. But idk where I would go from here. }) 32... Be6 { She decided to attack my h3 pawn this way instead of Bg2 which makes sense cause it defends f7 as well. } { [%clk 0:51:00] } 33. g6 { I liked this move. Finally breaking things up a bit. } { [%clk 0:25:00] } 33... fxg6 { [%clk 0:49:00] } (33... Bxh3 34. g7 { This would have been lost for black. }) 34. Nxg6 { And here I liked that both the h pawns trade off but I'm left with the passer on f4 } { [%clk 0:25:00] } 34... Bxh3 { [%clk 0:49:00] } 35. Nxh4 { [%clk 0:25:00] } 35... Be6 { [%clk 0:48:00] } 36. f5 { Push knight win space. Maybe it works with bishops too. } { [%clk 0:23:00] } 36... Bf7 { [%clk 0:48:00] } 37. Ng6 { Needed to bring my knight back somehow and I thought taking the knight would be catastrophic for black. } { [%clk 0:23:00] } 37... b4 { She had to try and create a passed pawn too at some point. } { [%clk 0:46:00] } (37... Bxg6 38. fxg6 Ke7 39. Kc5 Kf6 40. Kxb5 Kxg6 41. Kxc4 Kf5 42. Kb5 { GGs }) 38. axb4 { [%clk 0:22:00] } 38... axb4 { [%clk 0:46:00] } 39. Ne5 { This looked like a clear win for me. It wasn't clear at all but it looked like it :) } { [%clk 0:23:00] } 39... c3 {  } { [%clk 0:40:00] } 40. Nxf7+ { I thought this was very likely a win. If I managed to take her pawns and get back to mine in time. } { [%clk 0:51:00] } (40. bxc3 { Saw that this would end in a draw. } 40... bxc3 41. Nxf7+ Ke7 42. Kxc3 (42. Ne5 { Completely missed this. Ouch. }) 42... Kxf7 43. Kd4 Kf6 44. Ke4 { Draw }) 40... Ke7 { [%clk 1:10:00] } 41. bxc3 { [%clk 0:51:00] } 41... b3 { Completely missed this. } { [%clk 1:08:00] } (41... bxc3 42. Ne5 { This move I had seen tho and I was very happy as I realized here I'm definitely winning. }) 42. Kd3 { Only move } { [%clk 0:51:00] } 42... Kxf7 { [%clk 1:08:00] } 43. c4 { Also felt like an only move because she can promote otherwise. } { [%clk 0:49:00] } 43... b2 { [%clk 1:06:00] } 44. Kc2 { [%clk 0:50:00] } 44... b1=Q+ { [%clk 1:06:00] } 45. Kxb1 { [%clk 0:50:00] } 45... Kf6 { I calculated quite a bit to figure out if this would simplify into a winning king and pawn endgame. That said I also know the only way it would be was if I brought my king back up the board so I didn't stop for too long. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 46. Kc2 { My original plan was to go straight up the b file but going up the c file first allowed me the option to pass my pawn on the b or d files so I went for this. } { [%clk 0:49:00] } 46... Kxf5 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 47. Kc3 { [%clk 0:50:00] } 47... Ke6 { Here I thought for a minute because I was considering Kd4 but I didn't think that would win. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 48. Kb4 { Happy I didn't go d4 } { [%clk 0:49:00] } (48. Kd4 Kd6 49. c5+ Kc6 50. Kc4 $10 {  }) 48... Kd6 { [%clk 1:06:00] } 49. Kb5 { By now I knew it was winning but I was sweating a little because I didn't want to mess it up. } { [%clk 0:49:00] } 49... Kc7 { [%clk 1:06:00] } (49... Kd7 { I thought this might be better as I can't play Kc5 } 50. Kc5?? (50. Kb6 { This is what I would have played tho and been fine. }) 50... Kc7) 50. Kc5 { This is the exampled used to first introduce the concept of opposition so I finally relaxed. } { [%clk 0:50:00] } 50... Kd7 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 51. Kb6 { [%clk 0:50:00] } 51... Kc8 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 52. Kc6 { [%clk 0:50:00] } 52... Kd8 { [%clk 1:08:00] } 53. Kb7 { [%clk 0:51:00] } 53... Kd7 { [%clk 1:08:00] } 54. c5 { [%clk 0:51:00] } 1-0


