1. e4 { [%clk 1:30:00] } 1... c6 { [%clk 1:30:00] } 2. Nc3 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 2... d5 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 3. Nf3 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 3... Bg4 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 4. h3 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 4... Bh5 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 5. g4 { First mistake. IDK why I thought I had to play g4 before taking the d pawn. } { [%clk 1:31:00] } 5... Bg6 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 6. exd5 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 6... cxd5 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 7. Bb5+ { [%clk 1:31:00] } 7... Nc6 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 8. Ne5 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 8... Qd6 { [%clk 1:29:00] } 9. d4 { Up to here I thought I was playing all the right moves from my repertoire. } { [%clk 1:29:00] } 9... a6 { This move I had never seen or didn't remember looking at. } { [%clk 1:29:00] } 10. Bxc6+ { Felt like the only reasonable option. } { [%clk 1:29:00] } (10. Ba4 b5 11. Bb3 {  } 11... e6 { This seemed to make my bishop very very bad. }) (10. Bd3 { This was another move I briefly considered but it also didn't look too promising. } 10... Nxe5 11. dxe5 Qxe5+ 12. Be3 Bxd3 (12... d4 { I think trading on d3 first makes more sense for black }) 13. Qxd3 d4) 10... bxc6 { Here we transposed into my repertoire and I should have played Bf4. } { [%clk 1:29:00] } 11. Nxg6 { Here I took as I thought it was better to not leave black with the bishop pair. In hindsight I think my knight was very good on that square. } { [%clk 1:26:00] } 11... hxg6 { [%clk 1:27:00] } 12. Qf3 { Didn't really know how to develop my pieces here. I definitely wanted to castle queenside as I didn't like the structure I created on the kingside and I thought that by moving my queen first I could then develop my bishop to f4 with a tempo on the black queen. } { [%clk 1:25:00] } 12... Nf6 { [%clk 1:25:00] } 13. Bf4 { [%clk 1:25:00] } 13... Qb4 { I had failed to consider this move. I luckily realized that long castling would protect both attacked pawns but also place my king right in the line of fire of the queen and an eventual rook on b8. } { [%clk 1:24:00] } 14. O-O-O { Defends pawns but this is where I started getting a bit scared. Rb8 would be really bad for me so that made my bishop on f4 one of the most important pieces I had. } { [%clk 1:21:00] } 14... e6 { [%clk 1:23:00] } 15. h4 { IDK what the real idea with this move was. I felt like I was in trouble on the queenside but I couldn't really see what I should do about that so I thought slowly starting a bit of an attack on the kingside might work. } { [%clk 1:16:00] } 15... Bd6 { Quite logical move from black. My bishop on f4 was very important and trading it off could only really help black. } { [%clk 1:24:00] } 16. Bxd6 { That said by taking myself I force black to take back with the queen and waste a tempo in the future if he ever wanted to bring her back to b4. } { [%clk 1:15:00] } (16. h5 { I also realized that if I wasted time and let black take my bishop my queen would stop defending my knight. } 16... Bxf4+ 17. Qxf4 Rb8 18. b3 Qxc3 { Since b3 felt like a necessary option to keep for myself I didn't feel comfortable letting black take my bishop. }) 16... Qxd6 { [%clk 1:22:00] } 17. g5 { My plan was to play Na4 and then bring my queen to the queenside to help defend. I realized that this would leave my g4 pawn hanging so I thought this was a logical in between move. } { [%clk 1:12:00] } 17... Nd7 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 18. Na4 { [%clk 1:12:00] } 18... Rb8 { [%clk 1:19:00] } 19. Qc3 { [%clk 1:12:00] } 19... Rb4 { This move I hadn't seen. It looked pretty annoying but I felt I could still continue with my plan of Nc5 to try and trade down some pieces. } { [%clk 1:19:00] } 20. Nc5 { [%clk 1:11:00] } 20... Rc4 { Obviously another move I didn't see coming. Now I'd at least losing a pawn. } { [%clk 1:19:00] } 21. Qa5 { [%clk 1:11:00] } (21. Qa3 { Considered this too but I thought it was just worse as with Qa5 I threaten some kind of invasion with my queen if black doesn't start trading down pieces. }) 21... Nxc5 { [%clk 1:19:00] } 22. dxc5 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 22... Qxc5 { Took a decent think here. Trading seemed like a sad prospect as I would just be a pawn down in a rook endgame where black has very few weaknesses for me to attack. } { [%clk 1:19:00] } 23. Qxc5 { In the end I went with this because I felt that defending a rook endgame down a pawn was my best hope. Very possible to draw this imo. } { [%clk 1:08:00] } (23. Qxa6 Rxc2+ 24. Kb1 { Thought this might be decent as I am threatening to win the h8 rook } 24... O-O { But after O-O by black I couldn't really see anything good about my position. } (24... Rxf2 { Even here this idea might work } 25. Qc8+ Ke7 26. Qxh8 Qc2+ { Yep I can't win the rook on h8 as I get mated. }) 25. h5 gxh5 26. Rxh5 Rxf2 27. Rdh1 { Here I am too slow as black gets to play Qc2+ and mate. }) (23. Qd2 { This felt like an option too. Trying to defend c2. } 23... Rcxh4 24. Rxh4 Rxh4 { That said black is up two pawns here so I decided against it. }) 23... Rxc5 { [%clk 1:19:00] } 24. Rh3 { [%clk 1:08:00] } 24... Rc4 { Thought he was going to play this which is why I played Rh3 before. } { [%clk 1:19:00] } 25. Rdh1 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 25... Rg4 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 26. f3 { Here I saw his rook threatened nothing so I thought I would just kick it out. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 26... Rg2 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 27. b4 { Wanted to advance my king on the queenside and this seemed best as it allowed me to play Kb2 and Kb3 without having to move the pawn again later. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 27... Kd7 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 28. Kb2 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 28... Kd6 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 29. R1h2 { This I wasn't sure about. I have a vague memory of having heard that trading one rook (when you both have two) favors the winning side so not me in this case. That said, his rook on g2 created some problems for me so trading it off felt like a small win. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 29... Rxh2 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 30. Rxh2 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 30... c5 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 31. c3 { Only move that made sense to me. Taking worsens my pawn structure and allows him to bring his king even closer. I also like the prospect of having an a and b pawn against his lone a pawn potentially creating a passer in the future. Slight foreshadowing. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 31... cxb4 { [%clk 1:20:00] } 32. cxb4 { Exactly as I had hoped. Now I might create a passed pawn in the future. } { [%clk 1:08:00] } 32... e5 { [%clk 1:21:00] } 33. Kc3 { I realized that his two pawns coming down the center were a more imminent threat than my b pawn trading its way thru so I decided to bring my king closer. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 33... Rc8+ { Completely forgetting that this allows him to bring his rook with a tempo. } { [%clk 1:21:00] } 34. Kb3 { [%clk 1:07:00] } 34... Rc4 { [%clk 1:21:00] } 35. h5 { Only move that seemed logical to me. I have to try and open up something somewhere to create some potential for a blunder for black. } { [%clk 1:07:00] } (35. a4 { This with the intention of playing b4 made sense too but with his rook on c4 my king would never be able to come help that pawn. }) 35... Rf4?? { And here I almost played hxg6. Luckily I thought for a second and realized I can squeeze a pawn thru. } { [%clk 1:14:00] } 36. h6! { My opponent was a child (surprise surprise) and he spent the whole game walking around the room and our table and blitzing out each move. After I played h6 he finally sat down. :) } { [%clk 1:07:00] } 36... Rxf3+ { [%clk 1:14:00] } 37. Ka4 { In hindsight this was a loss of time. I should have calculated better and seen that after he goes Rc3 and Rc8 my king would be better on b2 where it doesn't block the a pawn. } { [%clk 0:58:00] } 37... gxh6 { [%clk 1:13:00] } 38. gxh6 { [%clk 0:58:00] } 38... Rc3 { [%clk 1:14:00] } 39. h7 { [%clk 0:59:00] } 39... Rc8 { [%clk 1:14:00] } 40. h8=Q { [%clk 1:29:00] } 40... Rxh8 { [%clk 1:44:00] } 41. Rxh8 { [%clk 1:29:00] } 41... e4 { Still pretty scary. I was very uncertain about what to do here. I considered all kinds of rook moves but they all felt like relative wastes of time. } { [%clk 1:45:00] } 42. Kb3 { I decided to bring my king backwards to add an eventual defender for all those damn pawns he had and also to open up the idea of playing a4 and b5 and creating another threat in the position. } { [%clk 1:25:00] } 42... Ke5 { [%clk 1:44:00] } 43. a4 { This felt so good to play. Completely ignoring his pawns and just pushing mine to create the obvious but unstoppable threat of making a queen. } { [%clk 1:24:00] } 43... d4 { [%clk 1:43:00] } 44. b5 { If he kept pushing his pawns on the d, e, f, and g files I would have all the time in the world to make a queen on b8 and I still always had the option to bring my rook down to the 1st rank to defend a promotion. On the other hand if he went for my pawn on the b file I would go eat all of his pawns with my king and rook and then we would be left with no pawns but I would have a rook. } { [%clk 1:24:00] } 1-0


